question: Abby has 14 jars of chocolate chips in her pantry. Each jar of chocolate chips can decorate 17 cookies. Abby wants to bake enough cookies to use up all of her chocolate chips. If each pan holds 14 cookies, how many pans worth of cookies should she bake?
answer:
She has enough chocolate chips for 14 * 17 = <<14*17=238>>238 cookies.
She needs 238 / 14 = <<238/14=17>>17 pans to bake all of the cookies.
#### 17
